#age.rb
puts "How old are you"
age=gets.chomp.to_i

puts "In ten years you will be:" 
puts age + 10
puts "In twenty years you will be:"
puts age + 20
puts "In thirty years you will be:"
puts age + 30
puts "In forty years you will be:"
puts age + 40

First prints 3
Second will return an error because x isn't defined within the right scope
